            HSBC Sterling Liquidity Fund


            HSBC Sterling Liquidity Fund
        





               HSBC Sterling Liquidity Fund
            










Fund objective
To provide investors with security of capital and daily liquidity together with an investment return which is comparable to normal sterling denominated money market interest rates.
Permitted investments
The fund may invest in certificates of deposit (CD), commercial paper, medium-term notes (MTNs), variable rate notes (VRNs), floating rate notes (FRNs), bankers acceptances, government bonds, treasury bills, Eurobonds, asset-backed securities and corporate bonds.
Credit rating
Short-term transferable securities which at the time of purchase have a credit rating of at least A-1/P-1 (or its equivalent) from a recognised credit rating agency such as Standard & Poor’s or Moody’s.



Fund details
            




Fund Rating
S&P – AAAm
            Moody’s - Aaa-mf


Fund manager
Philip Walsh & Florent Vassord (Paris)


Launch date
1 September 1999


Valuation date
Daily


Cut-off time
1:30 pm (Dublin time)


Settlement date
Same day


Dividend policy
Distributing





Disclaimer:

The HSBC Global Liquidity Funds plc offer offshore funds (“Liquidity Funds”) which are
managed by HSBC Global Asset Management (UK) Limited (“AMEU”). The Liquidity Funds
are offered in Canada through HSBC Global Asset Management (Canada) Limited (“AMCA”).
AMCA and AMEU are affiliated with HSBC Holdings plc. AMCA is a subsidiary of HSBC
Bank Canada. The Liquidity Funds are not guaranteed or covered by the Canadian Deposit
Insurance Corporation, any other deposit insurer or HSBC Bank Canada. The unit values of the
funds may not remain constant and past performance may not be repeated. The Liquidity Funds
are sold in Canada under exemptions with minimum required purchase amounts as well as other
requirements. As a purchaser of this offshore fund through the exempt market you may lose
certain legal rights and may be subject to different tax requirements as compared to Canadian
based funds offered through the non-exempt market. We recommend you consult with your legal
and tax advisor prior to making any purchase.

















