            HSBC Canadian Money Market Fund


            HSBC Canadian Money Market Fund
        





               HSBC Canadian Money Market Fund
            










Fund objective
The fundamental investment objective of this Fund is to provide a high level of monthly interest income while preserving capital by investing primarily in high-quality, short-term Canadian fixed income securities.
Permitted investments
The Fund invests primarily in treasury bills and other fixed income securities, either issued or guaranteed by the Government of Canada or a province of Canada, Canadian corporate  bonds and commercial paper, bankers’ acceptances, mortgages  or mortgage-backed securities, guaranteed investment certificates and cash. All of the Fund’s securities will have a maturity of less than 365 days, with an average term of no more than 60 days. A portion of the Fund’s holdings may be in the form of cash or cash equivalents. In limited circumstances, the Fund may invest the majority of its assets in cash or cash equivalents to preserve capital and provide liquidity. The Fund may invest up to 33% of its assets in foreign securities.
Credit rating
Bonds held in the Fund will generally be rated  ‘‘A’’ or better by Standard & Poor’s or DBRS Limited or an equivalent rating by another designated rating organization. Money market securities will generally be rated ‘‘A-1’’ or better by Standard & Poor’s, ‘‘R-1-L’’ or better by DBRS Limited or an equivalent rating by another designated rating organization.



Fund details
            




Fund Rating
N/A


Fund manager
Derek Amery (Canada)


Launch date
6 January 1989


Valuation date
Daily


Cut-off time
1:00 pm (Pacific Time); 4:00 pm (Eastern Standard Time)


Settlement date
T+1


Dividend policy
Reinvested





Mutual Fund Disclaimer:


HSBC Global Asset Management (Canada) Limited is the manager and primary investment advisor for the HSBC Mutual Funds.  HSBC Investment Funds (Canada) Inc. is the principal distributor of the HSBC Mutual Funds.  HSBC Mutual Funds are also distributed through authorized dealers.  Commissions, trailing commissions, management fees and expenses all may be associated with mutual fund investments.  Please read the prospectus before investing.  Mutual funds are not guaranteed or covered by the Canada Deposit Insurance Corporation, HSBC Bank Canada, or any other deposit insurer.  Their values change frequently and past performance may not be repeated. The unit value of money market funds may not remain constant.















